  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FCS Viva Fresh Kosovo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project is expected to have a positive development impact, the most significant expected Project-level impact is derived from: (i) economy-wide, employment and supply chain development effects through the expansion of the Company retail network and; (ii) stakeholder effects through improve access of local lower and middle-income consumers to a more affordable and diverse selection of high-quality food products. Beyond the Project, IFC investment will help companies along the supply chain in the Republic of Kosovo to integrate into domestic supply chain.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment is a senior secured corporate loan to Viva Fresh sh.p.k (the Company or Viva Fresh) that will be used to fund the Companys medium-term retail expansion plan. Founded in 2002, the Company is the largest food and non-food physical retailer in the Republic of Kosovo having a diversified portfolio of fast-moving consumer goods, fresh foods, fashion, footwear, and home goods categories.&#xA0;At the end of September 2019, the store network operating under the Viva Fresh Store banner comprised 63 units, of which one in Skopje, Republic of North Macedonia.</narrative>
  </description>
